---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const utilities = [
  'Daycare for owners who need a clean half-day handoff before lunch or an event.',
  'Boarding options when the Peninsula trip includes dog-free windows.',
  'Groomers and pet retail for practical reset needs, not lifestyle fluff.',
  'Pet-supply stops that solve forgotten-lead, food, toy, or cleanup problems quickly.',
];
---

<BaseLayout title="Dog Daycare, Boarding, Groomers and Pet Shops Mornington Peninsula | Peninsula Insider" description="Utility guide to dog daycare, boarding, groomers and pet shops on the Mornington Peninsula." section="explore">
  <main class="article-shell container prose" style="padding: 3rem 0 4rem; max-width: 820px;">
    <p class="label label--accent">Dog-Friendly Peninsula</p>
    <h1>Dog Daycare, Boarding, Groomers and Pet Shops on the Mornington Peninsula</h1>
    <p>Dog-owner utility is where most travel guides fall apart. The glamorous part is easy. The practical layer is what determines whether the trip still works when plans change.</p>
    <ul>
      {utilities.map((item) => <li>{item}</li>)}
    </ul>
    <p>This page should become the Peninsula’s practical owner-support directory, tightly edited rather than bloated.</p>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
